To set up a virtual environment:
python -m venv myenv


To activate the virtual environment:


.\myenv\Scripts\activate


To activate the virtual environment in Bash , use:
source myenv/bin/activate



If you're using Git Bash on Windows, you might need:
source myenv/Scripts/activate


# After activation, you should see (myenv) 

pip install requests


python app.py
 


